        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 12:04AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 1203 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Taylor, or 16 miles east of Cortland, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Otselic, Cuyler, Georgetown, Pitcher, Pharsalia, Deruyter, Taylor,
Lincklaen, Smyrna, and De Ruyter.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
